steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Mash the bananas
- Lightly beat the eggs
- Lightly Spray a 9x5" loaf pan with cooking spray

### Steps
- Put rack in the middle of the oven
- Preheat to 350F
- Place flour, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl
- Whisk to combine
- Place the sugar and butter into stand mixer (or use a bowl and a hand mixer), beat on medium speed till fluffy and lightened in color.
- Add the banana and eggs and beat until thoroughly incorporated 
- Scrape the sides of the bowl
- With the mixer on low speed, slowly add the flour until just combined (**DO NOT OVER MIX**)
- Divide in half to make two loafs
- Bake for 40 to 50 minutes
- Let it cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes
- After that let it cool out of the pan on the wire rack till fully cooled

#### Notes
- Frozen bananas: Whole frozen bananas can be used in this recipe. Thaw the bananas, then squeeze them right out of the peels; no need for mashing!
- Storage: Leftover banana bread can be tightly wrapped in plastic wrap and stored at room temperature for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.
